Welcome to the start of a new school year! We realize this has been, and continues to be, a deeply unsettling time for communities across our country. Though many things are still uncertain, please rest assured that students‚Äô education at K12-powered schools is not one of them.

In the midst of seeing unprecedented interest in our programs, our teams have been hard at work strengthening operations to better serve each student‚Äôs learning needs. Please know that any initial challenges students may face will be resolved in the coming days and weeks.

Please refer to communication from your school regarding important instructions during the high volume start to this school year, and please continue to check the K12 Help Page for updates: http://ow.ly/ZNwI50BikR8.

We are excited about the great things to come throughout this new school year, as we continue to serve our growing school community!

Registered Kids Receive 2 FREE GAMES Of Bowling Each Day Of The KBF Program All Summer Long, Valued At Over $500 Per Child!
Select bowling centers and schools around the country are participating in the first ever Kids Bowl Free program. This program is designed by bowling centers to give back to the community and provide a safe, secure, and fun way for kids to spend time this summer.

post_text:
Have you checked out K12's summer camps? Online summer camps are a great way to connect to your school community and with other students across the country! These free virtual camps are scheduled from June through August and last anywhere from 30 minutes to one hour per session. Once you register, Summer Camp sessions for your grade level will be available in your Online School each week on Monday morning.

We offer camps at multiple times to accommodate different time zones and family schedules, so you can attend the day and time that works best for you. Your child can attend one or many of these fun programs to make new friends, explore a new interest, and have fun!

Here is the K12 Summer Camp brochure: https://www.k12.com/content/dam/k12/pdf/K12SummerCampsFlyer_2020.pdf. Click here to sign up:

https://bit.ly/2020K12Camps.

See you at one of our virtual camps soon!

June 3 at 11:57 AM ¬∑

We‚Äôve got something we want you to know.

Our belief in equal treatment and opportunity is unwavering, as is our commitment to providing a platform for all voices to find expression and be heard. This is true today and every day.

Now, more than ever, kids need a safe place to explore, discover, understand and find their voice. Through content that showcases diverse cultural experiences and by encouraging acceptance, understanding, empathy and inclusion, we can help this and future generations of kids become educated, open-minded and kind to one another.

For more information, helpful resources and curated book collections on race and social justice, please read our recent blog post: https://www.getepic.com/learn/epic-a-safe-place-to-explore-all-voices/
